### Introduction to OpenCTI

OpenCTI is an open-source platform allowing for organizations to manage their cyber threat intelligence knowloedge and observables. It enables security professionals to store, organize and visualize threat intelligence related to cyber threats.
OpenCTI can be integrated with other frameworks and tools such as MISP and Mitre ATT@CK.

---

### Features

The goal is to create a comprehensive tool allowing users to capitalize technical (such as TTPs and observables) and non-technical information (such as suggested attribution, victimology etc.) while linking each piece of information to its primary source (a report, a MISP event, etc.), with features such as links between each information, first and last seen dates, levels of confidence, etc. IT acts a centralized hub to collect intelligence from multiple sources.

With connectors and workers, analysts can automate data ingestion and enrichment, reducing manual effort and speeding up detection. It enables OpenCTO to make a connection to several other platforms and tools such as:
- SIEMs (splunk, ELK)
- MITRE ATT&CK
- MISP
- External feeds like VirusTotal

OpenCTI uses the STIX 2.1 standard for threat intelligence. That means the data is machine-readable, easily sharable.

